article.headline: Prairie View 88, Grambling St. 78
article.story: PRAIRIE VIEW, Texas (AP) -- Aaron Smith scored 30 points and Prairie View won consecutive games for only the second time this season by beating Grambling State 88-78 on Monday night. Freddie Edo added 16 points to help Prairie View (7-17, 5-7 SWAC) sweep the season series against the Tigers (6-14, 6-7). Jamal Breaux scored 19 points to lead Grambling State, which lost its second straight after having a five-game winning streak snapped Saturday. Smith shot 9-of-17 from the field in scoring a single-game season high for the Panthers. Brian Ezeh added 12 points for Prairie View.
